==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: peacekeeper
<hw>peacekeeper</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a member of a
military force that is assigned (often with international sanction) to
preserve peace in a trouble area.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>someone who keeps peace; <as>as, she's the
<ex>peacekeeper</ex> in that family</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>the pistol of a law officer in the old West.</def>
<mark>[U. S. History]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peaceless</ent>⟦br⟧
